WEBVTT

00:00:20.087 --> 00:00:22.756
[BORUTO] <i>Damn it! I can't use</i>
<i>jutsu like this.</i>

00:00:22.789 --> 00:00:24.758
Sorry, it's all my fault.

00:00:24.791 --> 00:00:26.927
Hey, Old Man! What's the
deal?!

00:00:26.960 --> 00:00:28.829
Now that you've captured us...

00:00:28.862 --> 00:00:30.631
just what are you gonna do
with us?

00:00:30.664 --> 00:00:32.366
Why, nothing!

00:00:32.399 --> 00:00:35.102
I just want to keep you out of
the way...

00:00:35.135 --> 00:00:37.337
so you don't make trouble until
the plan's been completed...

00:00:37.371 --> 00:00:38.338
that's all.

00:00:38.372 --> 00:00:41.375
Yes... We don't like
troublesome brats.

00:00:41.408 --> 00:00:43.644
Till we do something about those
Fabrications

00:00:43.677 --> 00:00:44.745
or whatever they are...

00:00:44.778 --> 00:00:47.047
we can't stop Old Man Ohnoki.

00:00:51.752 --> 00:00:55.222
Ah, ha! You can see the
village now.

00:00:55.255 --> 00:00:59.059
None of you will be harmed as
long as you behave and-

00:01:11.038 --> 00:01:12.539
What is this?!

00:01:16.043 --> 00:01:26.053
♪♪ (JAPANESE THEME MUSIC)

00:01:26.086 --> 00:01:36.096
♪♪ (JAPANESE THEME MUSIC)

00:01:36.129 --> 00:01:46.039
♪♪ (JAPANESE THEME MUSIC)

00:01:46.073 --> 00:01:56.083
♪♪ (JAPANESE THEME MUSIC)

00:01:56.116 --> 00:02:06.059
♪♪ (JAPANESE THEME MUSIC)

00:02:06.093 --> 00:02:16.069
♪♪ (JAPANESE THEME MUSIC)

00:02:16.103 --> 00:02:26.046
♪♪ (JAPANESE THEME MUSIC)

00:02:26.079 --> 00:02:36.089
♪♪ (JAPANESE THEME MUSIC)

00:02:36.123 --> 00:02:46.066
♪♪ (JAPANESE THEME MUSIC)

00:02:46.099 --> 00:02:51.038
♪♪ (JAPANESE THEME MUSIC)

00:03:01.315 --> 00:03:05.252
Wait, what's going on? It's
empty! There's nobody here!

00:03:05.285 --> 00:03:08.589
Just what is the meaning of all
this, Kirara?

00:03:08.622 --> 00:03:11.425
You'll have to ask Lord Ku
himself about it.

00:03:18.432 --> 00:03:20.133
(CURIOUS)

00:03:23.270 --> 00:03:25.072
(BOWING)

00:03:34.748 --> 00:03:38.051
I welcome you home, my Master.

00:03:38.085 --> 00:03:39.987
We ran into some small
obstacles...

00:03:40.020 --> 00:03:43.457
but now the plan is going
smoothly.

00:03:43.490 --> 00:03:45.726
Going smoothly, eh?

00:03:45.759 --> 00:03:49.296
Yes. The production of
Akuta is proceeding faster...

00:03:49.329 --> 00:03:51.331
than our original estimate.

00:03:51.365 --> 00:03:54.134
And the problems that had arisen
have all been dealt with-

00:03:54.168 --> 00:03:56.870
[OHNOKI] Then why is there no
one in the village?!

00:03:56.904 --> 00:04:00.107
And why are there Akuta out
walking through the streets?!

00:04:00.908 --> 00:04:02.109
Master...?

00:04:02.743 --> 00:04:04.111
Tell me...

00:04:04.144 --> 00:04:10.317
What the hell were you thinking
with all of this, Ku?!

00:04:10.350 --> 00:04:14.221
The situation changed greatly
while you were gone, Master.

00:04:14.254 --> 00:04:16.123
<i>That's why we've now</i>
<i>taken control...</i>

00:04:16.156 --> 00:04:18.091
<i>of the Hidden Stone Village.</i>

00:04:19.259 --> 00:04:21.261
<i>[OHNOKI] Taken control?!</i>

00:04:21.295 --> 00:04:26.099
The Akuta Plan is a measure to
be used only in an emergency!

00:04:27.801 --> 00:04:31.071
Why did you feel you needed to
take control of the village?

00:04:33.073 --> 00:04:35.809
Because the transient lives
that we'd been given...

00:04:35.843 --> 00:04:37.778
are just about to run out, sir.

00:04:37.811 --> 00:04:39.012
Can't be!

00:04:40.113 --> 00:04:42.649
The deterioration wasn't
supposed to occur this soon!

00:04:42.683 --> 00:04:44.418
I've enacted countermeasures.

00:04:45.285 --> 00:04:46.954
What?!

00:04:46.987 --> 00:04:48.789
We've already secured several
humans...

00:04:48.822 --> 00:04:50.991
whose hearts will soon
become ours.

00:04:51.024 --> 00:04:54.294
Is he saying that he's gonna
transplant the hearts...

00:04:54.328 --> 00:04:55.963
taken out of living people?

00:04:55.996 --> 00:04:57.197
What?! No way!

00:04:57.231 --> 00:04:59.833
I mean, if they do something
like that, then...

00:04:59.867 --> 00:05:01.502
what would happen to the
human donors?

00:05:01.535 --> 00:05:02.402
What is going on?

00:05:03.570 --> 00:05:05.105
Wasn't the whole point of
creating you Fabrications...

00:05:05.138 --> 00:05:08.208
...in the first place
to maintain a peaceful world?

00:05:08.242 --> 00:05:11.078
All we need now is your final
approval, Master.

00:05:11.111 --> 00:05:14.081
There's no way I would ever
allow such a thing!

00:05:14.114 --> 00:05:17.284
This is just a necessary
sacrifice for the greater good!

00:05:17.317 --> 00:05:19.453
You reached the same conclusion,
Master--

00:05:19.486 --> 00:05:22.789
What are you saying? The whole
point of our plan...

00:05:22.823 --> 00:05:26.159
has always been to prevent the
sacrifice of young lives!

00:05:26.193 --> 00:05:29.663
What you're suggesting we try to
do is the exact opposite

00:05:29.696 --> 00:05:31.331
of what my plan is all about!

00:05:31.365 --> 00:05:34.334
But Master... in order to
continue with the plan,

00:05:34.368 --> 00:05:37.070
the strength that we possess
is essential.

00:05:37.905 --> 00:05:40.374
[KU] <i>Not a minute can be wasted.</i>

00:05:40.407 --> 00:05:44.244
(SHOCKED) I'll think of another
solution.

00:05:44.278 --> 00:05:48.382
Anyway, go release those in
custody immediately.

00:05:48.415 --> 00:05:51.752
I'm sorry, but I cannot leave
you in command any longer.

00:05:55.422 --> 00:05:56.423
Please, wait.

00:05:56.924 --> 00:05:58.725
What is it now?

00:05:58.759 --> 00:06:02.162
There was a time, Master, when
you explained to me...

00:06:02.196 --> 00:06:05.098
...that we Fabrications were to
be your arms and your legs.

00:06:06.266 --> 00:06:07.968
<i>That to create the ideal</i>
<i>world...</i>

00:06:08.001 --> 00:06:10.070
<i>we'll be the substitutes</i>
<i>who'll do the work.</i>

00:06:11.905 --> 00:06:14.107
<i>So now, when those arms and</i>
<i>legs</i>

00:06:14.141 --> 00:06:15.175
<i>are about to disintegrate...</i>

00:06:16.443 --> 00:06:18.979
<i>...who will take our place</i>
<i>to fulfill your dream?</i>

00:06:19.012 --> 00:06:21.381
We have nothing more to talk
about!

00:06:21.415 --> 00:06:25.085
Master, does this mean...
that you're telling us to die?

00:06:25.752 --> 00:06:26.753
(CURIOUS)

00:06:27.588 --> 00:06:29.089
(PUNCHED IN GUT)

00:06:32.292 --> 00:06:33.327
Old Man!

00:06:33.360 --> 00:06:34.094
(SHOCKED)

00:06:36.463 --> 00:06:37.497
Lord Ohnoki! No!

00:06:37.531 --> 00:06:38.799
(ANGRY GROWL)

00:06:38.832 --> 00:06:40.901
Oh my, now he's done it...

00:06:40.934 --> 00:06:42.769
Is this really alright, Lord Ku?

00:06:42.803 --> 00:06:47.074
The Master's wish is supposed to
be our wish, as well.

00:06:48.075 --> 00:06:51.044
The Master is temporarily not in
his right mind.

00:06:51.078 --> 00:06:52.279
Nothing has changed.

00:06:52.312 --> 00:06:54.481
We're back together with the
Master once again.

00:06:54.515 --> 00:06:57.117
Begin preparations for the
transplants.

00:06:57.150 --> 00:06:58.585
[KOKUYOU] <i>What about them?</i>

00:06:58.619 --> 00:06:59.620
[KU] <i>Do as you please.</i>

00:07:00.621 --> 00:07:02.089
Quit messing around!

00:07:02.623 --> 00:07:03.824
You know too much.

00:07:03.857 --> 00:07:07.995
Every hindrance, no matter how
small, must be eliminated.

00:07:08.028 --> 00:07:11.265
Wonderful! Because I
just found something pretty!

00:07:11.932 --> 00:07:13.433
(SCOFFING HARRUMPH)

00:07:13.467 --> 00:07:14.668
I thought that...

00:07:14.701 --> 00:07:18.272
the Old Man created you guys to
protect humans, didn't he?!

00:07:18.305 --> 00:07:20.574
So why are you planning on
hurting them, then?!

00:07:20.607 --> 00:07:23.577
It's not our place to
think about such things.

00:07:23.610 --> 00:07:24.845
How can you say that?!

00:07:24.878 --> 00:07:27.981
I'm certain that you guys must
have a will- and a heart, too!

00:07:28.015 --> 00:07:31.652
A heart? No,... we
have no such thing.

00:07:31.685 --> 00:07:37.391
And that's why we Fabrications
are far superior to you humans.

00:07:37.424 --> 00:07:39.459
(FRUSTRATED)

00:07:39.493 --> 00:07:40.627
(WORRIED)

00:07:43.263 --> 00:07:45.499
Give up and die already!

00:07:45.532 --> 00:07:46.633
(ATTACKING YELL)

00:07:50.737 --> 00:07:52.406
[AKUTA] (FRIGHTENED YELL)

00:08:02.249 --> 00:08:03.483
[SHIKADAI] <i>Over here!</i>

00:08:03.517 --> 00:08:04.484
(SHOCKED)

00:08:05.619 --> 00:08:06.420
[BORUTO] <i>Shikadai!</i>

00:08:07.287 --> 00:08:08.589
(EXCITED)

00:08:08.622 --> 00:08:10.991
The Akuta are guarding the
captive Hidden Stone Shinobi...

00:08:11.024 --> 00:08:12.993
so they're shorthanded.

00:08:13.026 --> 00:08:15.095
Let's get out of here while we
still can!

00:08:24.071 --> 00:08:25.472
Well, it looks like...

00:08:25.506 --> 00:08:28.108
I'm gonna get to pay you back
properly now.

00:08:28.141 --> 00:08:30.644
So, you returned to look for
your final resting place?

00:08:30.677 --> 00:08:33.113
I shall be glad to assist you!

00:08:33.146 --> 00:08:36.083
Alright, it's about time we turn
the tables on this guy.

00:08:36.116 --> 00:08:39.219
(SIGH) I guess the majority
has spoken.

00:08:39.253 --> 00:08:42.289
Boruto and Sarada, you
get going and find Mitsuki.

00:08:42.322 --> 00:08:44.291
He oughta be over in
their hideout.

00:08:44.324 --> 00:08:46.293
Just don't be reckless,
Shikadai.

00:08:46.326 --> 00:08:49.630
(CHUCKLE) Seriously, have I ever
done anything like that before?

00:08:59.439 --> 00:09:01.141
(CONFUSED)

00:09:05.078 --> 00:09:07.080
(DETERMINED)

00:09:09.416 --> 00:09:10.417
[INOJIN] <i>Stop!</i>

00:09:11.451 --> 00:09:12.586
He was on your side!

00:09:15.322 --> 00:09:16.490
Very cute.

00:09:16.523 --> 00:09:19.793
But they're completely useless
in a real battle.

00:09:19.826 --> 00:09:21.061
(FRUSTRATED)

00:09:21.094 --> 00:09:23.564
I'm gonna have to seal you away
right now.

00:09:23.597 --> 00:09:24.998
(CHUCKLE)

00:09:27.601 --> 00:09:28.602
(SHOCKED)

00:09:34.274 --> 00:09:35.242
(ANGRY)

00:09:37.077 --> 00:09:38.078
(DETERMINED)

00:09:44.918 --> 00:09:47.120
[KIRARA] <i>Oh, taking a little</i>
<i>stroll?</i>

00:09:50.424 --> 00:09:54.895
Damn, you took a shortcut, huh?
She's gonna use genjutsu on us!

00:09:54.928 --> 00:09:56.129
I got it.

00:09:57.631 --> 00:10:00.467
I just love pretty things!

00:10:00.501 --> 00:10:03.103
And I think those eyeglasses
would look far better on me

00:10:03.136 --> 00:10:04.838
than they ever would on you!

00:10:04.872 --> 00:10:08.075
Shut up! Like I'd just
give 'em to you!

00:10:08.108 --> 00:10:11.478
Ah... Then I have no choice but
to take them from you.

00:10:11.512 --> 00:10:14.481
You see, all pretty things
belong to me.

00:10:14.515 --> 00:10:15.415
Hold on...

00:10:16.617 --> 00:10:20.787
is she collecting things so she
can seem to be more human?

00:10:20.821 --> 00:10:22.089
(CONFUSED)

00:10:24.591 --> 00:10:25.826
(SHOCKED)

00:10:25.859 --> 00:10:27.628
[KIRARA] <i>Let's play... dollies!</i>

00:10:27.661 --> 00:10:30.097
(GASP)

00:10:41.241 --> 00:10:44.077
You really thought an aerial
attack would be effective?

00:10:47.648 --> 00:10:48.448
(CONFIDENT CHUCKLE)

00:10:53.253 --> 00:10:55.489
If you're in the air, then you
can't dodge!

00:10:56.423 --> 00:10:58.959
(THROWING)

00:10:58.992 --> 00:11:00.127
(SHOCKED)

00:11:03.931 --> 00:11:05.432
(FRUSTRATED)

00:11:14.408 --> 00:11:16.176
I thought so.

00:11:16.210 --> 00:11:20.480
It seems that you cannot use
your jutsu in the darkness.

00:11:20.514 --> 00:11:21.582
(SHOCKED)

00:11:23.817 --> 00:11:25.919
Is this all you're capable of?

00:11:25.953 --> 00:11:27.588
Shikadai!

00:11:27.621 --> 00:11:30.824
You two possess jutsu unsuited
for close combat.

00:11:30.858 --> 00:11:33.961
So, the true foe must be...

00:11:33.994 --> 00:11:36.997
(ATTACKING YELL)

00:11:37.931 --> 00:11:39.266
(SLAMMING INTO WALL)

00:11:40.601 --> 00:11:42.236
(ATTENTION IS CAUGHT)

00:11:42.736 --> 00:11:44.238
(WORRIED)

00:11:47.608 --> 00:11:48.909
Are you guys okay?

00:11:48.942 --> 00:11:52.045
Uh, I guess you could call it
"okay..."

00:11:52.079 --> 00:11:53.080
[KOKUYOU] Too bad.

00:11:54.815 --> 00:11:57.084
It seems that I overestimated
you.

00:11:57.584 --> 00:11:58.585
(ANGRY)

00:11:59.686 --> 00:12:02.155
After seeing your strength in
our previous battle...

00:12:02.189 --> 00:12:04.157
I was looking forward to this.

00:12:04.191 --> 00:12:07.961
But to think, this is all you
have to offer...

00:12:07.995 --> 00:12:09.129
Huh?!

00:12:12.266 --> 00:12:14.134
<i>Damn it, what do we do?</i>

00:12:14.168 --> 00:12:17.271
We don't have anything to give
<i>us an edge...</i>

00:12:17.304 --> 00:12:21.375
<i>One of us'll just have to</i>
<i>take a risk...</i>

00:12:21.408 --> 00:12:23.777
[SHIKADAI] <i>The knight will</i>
<i>become the gold general...</i>

00:12:23.810 --> 00:12:24.778
(TAKEN BACK)

00:12:24.811 --> 00:12:26.747
Shikadai, are you gonna--?!

00:12:28.615 --> 00:12:32.319
(ATTACKING)

00:12:32.352 --> 00:12:34.454
(RUNNING)

00:12:34.488 --> 00:12:38.625
Sacrificing yourself to save
your friends, eh?

00:12:38.659 --> 00:12:41.728
There's no time. I have to end
this quickly.

00:12:41.762 --> 00:12:42.763
(SHOCKED)

00:13:00.280 --> 00:13:03.116
We're supposed to get
ready for the transplants now!

00:13:03.150 --> 00:13:06.153
Oh, that's good to hear. I'll
prepare right away...

00:13:10.791 --> 00:13:13.894
This is all thanks to the data
from your heart, Mitsuki.

00:13:13.927 --> 00:13:17.397
This is the second time that
you've saved us.

00:13:17.431 --> 00:13:19.366
It's nothing.

00:13:19.399 --> 00:13:22.603
In humans, the heart pounds fast
even during happy times, right?

00:13:22.636 --> 00:13:25.639
I wonder what that's
like. I can't wait to feel it!

00:13:27.307 --> 00:13:31.144
Once I get a heart, I want you
to teach me all sorts of things!

00:13:31.178 --> 00:13:34.114
Because we'll be able to
stay together for a long time!

00:13:49.162 --> 00:13:52.165
Any news on contacting those
sent to another location?

00:13:54.134 --> 00:13:55.135
(MENACING GROWLS)

00:13:55.169 --> 00:14:00.174
(WORRIED CHATTER)

00:14:00.207 --> 00:14:03.143
Damn it! We can't make a move
while they have hostages...

00:14:04.645 --> 00:14:14.121
(HEAVY BREATHING)

00:14:17.658 --> 00:14:21.028
Sacrificing oneself for the sake
of others...

00:14:21.061 --> 00:14:24.198
You humans are creatures
beyond my understanding.

00:14:24.231 --> 00:14:27.000
(CHUCKLE) I know an
idiot who insists...

00:14:27.034 --> 00:14:29.303
that friends always help each
other...

00:14:29.336 --> 00:14:31.638
...no matter how difficult the
situation.

00:14:31.672 --> 00:14:34.474
Even though it's a drag!

00:14:34.508 --> 00:14:35.576
(KICKED)

00:14:35.609 --> 00:14:37.077
(HITTING THE GROUND)

00:14:37.110 --> 00:14:39.646
Those relationships only serve
to weaken you!

00:14:40.314 --> 00:14:41.114
(THROWING)

00:14:43.350 --> 00:14:44.151
(WORRIED)

00:14:45.285 --> 00:14:47.287
Can't think clearly now that
you're trapped?

00:14:47.654 --> 00:14:48.889
Damn it!

00:14:48.922 --> 00:14:51.158
Blame and curse your own
weakness!

00:14:52.960 --> 00:14:54.161
(TAKEN BACK)

00:14:57.164 --> 00:14:59.099
(STUNNED) What?!

00:14:59.132 --> 00:15:01.201
[INOJIN] <i>We got it to work</i>
<i>somehow!</i>

00:15:01.235 --> 00:15:04.104
Yeah, just as I expected.

00:15:04.137 --> 00:15:07.574
You mean that you planned this
trap from the beginning?!

00:15:07.608 --> 00:15:10.978
There's no way that any of us
can keep up with your speed.

00:15:11.011 --> 00:15:13.280
But you since aren't able to use
any jutsu...

00:15:13.313 --> 00:15:16.350
I figured you wouldn't use
long-distance attacks either.

00:15:16.383 --> 00:15:17.417
(ANGRY)

00:15:17.451 --> 00:15:19.887
If you can get close enough to
an enemy...

00:15:19.920 --> 00:15:21.688
even a knight can be a gold
general.

00:15:21.722 --> 00:15:30.831
(FRUSTRATED)

00:15:30.864 --> 00:15:34.968
I can't keep this up... Cho-Cho!
Make sure you get it done!

00:15:35.002 --> 00:15:38.438
I got this! Partial
Expansion Jutsu!

00:15:38.772 --> 00:15:39.973
(PUNCHED)

00:15:43.110 --> 00:15:45.045
When a lady's been insulted...

00:15:45.078 --> 00:15:48.048
it's her duty to pay it back
double, am I right?

00:15:48.081 --> 00:15:52.653
I'd say you did a lot more than
just double right now...

00:15:52.686 --> 00:15:55.522
Watch out!

00:15:55.556 --> 00:15:57.124
(SLAMMING INTO WALL)

00:16:00.327 --> 00:16:01.128
(NOTICING)

00:16:03.330 --> 00:16:07.134
(STRUGGLING) This was just a
transient life, after all, eh?

00:16:07.167 --> 00:16:10.871
Well, then... I will gladly
offer myself up.

00:16:10.904 --> 00:16:15.108
All right... show me just how
strong you are!

00:16:18.478 --> 00:16:19.279
Damn it!

00:16:23.283 --> 00:16:24.451
[KONOHAMARU] <i>What is this?</i>

00:16:26.453 --> 00:16:30.457
An underground facility? What
<i>are they planning here?</i>

00:16:31.658 --> 00:16:32.459
(ATTENTION IS CAUGHT)

00:16:35.662 --> 00:16:36.663
(SENSING SOMETHING)

00:16:44.938 --> 00:16:48.075
What, are you just going to
hide?

00:16:48.108 --> 00:16:50.677
Cho-Cho, we just need
one more hit.

00:16:50.711 --> 00:16:52.145
Can you punch him again?

00:16:52.179 --> 00:16:55.349
Well, when you put it like that,
how can I say no?

00:16:55.382 --> 00:16:56.216
But, wait...

00:16:57.384 --> 00:16:58.485
my Super Beast Scroll isn't
gonna work on him anymore!

00:16:59.653 --> 00:17:01.855
I know. But you still have
another jutsu you can use...

00:17:01.889 --> 00:17:03.657
remember?

00:17:03.690 --> 00:17:07.494
No way! And besides... it might
not even work on that guy...

00:17:08.462 --> 00:17:10.330
Well, we don't have another
option.

00:17:10.364 --> 00:17:13.133
It's all or nothing, you guys!

00:17:15.936 --> 00:17:17.437
(ATTENTION IS CAUGHT)

00:17:17.471 --> 00:17:19.473
[CHO-CHO] (THROWING)

00:17:19.506 --> 00:17:22.309
(THROWING)

00:17:22.342 --> 00:17:26.313
The same trick again? At such a
crucial moment?

00:17:27.481 --> 00:17:28.282
Useless!

00:17:28.982 --> 00:17:30.184
(CONFIDENT CHUCKLE)

00:17:30.784 --> 00:17:31.985
(SHOCKED)

00:17:32.853 --> 00:17:35.455
I totally can't believe it
worked!

00:17:35.489 --> 00:17:40.294
Nice. The Yamanaka Clan's Secret
Ninjutsu, Mind Transfer Jutsu...

00:17:40.327 --> 00:17:43.297
It does leave my real body
completely defenseless, though.

00:17:45.632 --> 00:17:46.667
(FALLS BACK)

00:17:46.700 --> 00:17:47.835
Can you hurry?

00:17:47.868 --> 00:17:50.070
I can't keep this up
for long!

00:17:50.103 --> 00:17:51.104
[CHO-CHO] <i>I'm on it!</i>

00:17:52.139 --> 00:17:55.976
I'm totally gonna beat him up!
Human Boulder!

00:17:57.444 --> 00:17:58.612
(GASP)

00:17:58.645 --> 00:18:00.981
(DETERMINED YELL)

00:18:01.014 --> 00:18:02.149
(SHOCKED)

00:18:04.651 --> 00:18:05.919
(STIRRING AWAKE)

00:18:05.953 --> 00:18:07.120
[SHIKADAI] Not good! (leaping)

00:18:08.622 --> 00:18:09.623
(SLAMMING)

00:18:09.957 --> 00:18:11.325
Cho-Cho!

00:18:11.358 --> 00:18:13.994
To think you still had a trick
like this up your sleeve!

00:18:14.027 --> 00:18:16.463
Aw, man! Guess it's not over
yet.

00:18:20.667 --> 00:18:22.436
I won't let you use that again!

00:18:28.475 --> 00:18:30.143
(ATTACKING YELL)

00:18:30.444 --> 00:18:31.478
Oh, no!

00:18:31.512 --> 00:18:32.679
(STRUGGLING)

00:18:32.713 --> 00:18:34.448
(CONFUSED) What? Let
go!

00:18:35.349 --> 00:18:36.517
(GASP)

00:18:36.550 --> 00:18:39.686
(STRUGGLING)

00:18:39.720 --> 00:18:41.021
It's now or never, Cho-Cho!

00:18:41.455 --> 00:18:42.656
Yeah, I know!

00:18:43.824 --> 00:18:49.196
You're in my way! Get lost!

00:18:49.229 --> 00:18:50.163
Akkun!

00:18:50.531 --> 00:18:51.665
(SURPRISED)

00:18:51.698 --> 00:18:53.867
Roll, roll, roll, roll, roll,
roll, roll, roll, roll!

00:18:53.901 --> 00:18:55.002
(SLAMMED)

00:19:06.113 --> 00:19:08.649
Looks like this match
is really over this time.

00:19:09.449 --> 00:19:10.684
You humans...

00:19:10.717 --> 00:19:15.489
are supposed to be weaklings
that need us to protect you...

00:19:15.522 --> 00:19:20.093
How can you fight in a way that
exposes yourself to danger?

00:19:20.127 --> 00:19:24.131
You're really strong.
Honestly, stronger than us.

00:19:24.164 --> 00:19:27.000
We have to compensate by
using another kind of strength

00:19:27.034 --> 00:19:29.136
to make up for the difference.

00:19:29.169 --> 00:19:31.438
Another kind of strength?

00:19:31.471 --> 00:19:33.507
That's right. The strength of
the heart.

00:19:33.540 --> 00:19:34.474
It's because...

00:19:35.709 --> 00:19:37.511
we're able to put our lives into
the hands of our friends...

00:19:37.544 --> 00:19:40.480
friends that we trust in with
all of our heart.

00:19:40.514 --> 00:19:43.350
Friends you trust with all of
your heart?

00:19:43.383 --> 00:19:46.320
I do not possess a
heart to begin with!

00:19:46.353 --> 00:19:48.956
The Mind Transfer Jutsu takes
over one's heart.

00:19:48.989 --> 00:19:51.158
And since that jutsu worked on
you...

00:19:51.191 --> 00:19:54.494
it proves that you
actually do have one.

00:19:55.128 --> 00:19:58.665
(STUNNED) I see...

00:20:08.275 --> 00:20:10.143
[INOJIN] <i>Why'd you come here?</i>

00:20:10.978 --> 00:20:12.346
I mean, you...

00:20:12.379 --> 00:20:14.982
you should've known you'd just
end up being a burden!

00:20:15.015 --> 00:20:16.316
(WEAK COOING)

00:20:16.350 --> 00:20:17.651
Huh?

00:20:18.452 --> 00:20:19.620
(LOVING COOS)

00:20:19.653 --> 00:20:24.358
Stop copying me. What do
you think you're doing, dummy?

00:20:24.391 --> 00:20:25.158
(WEAK COOING)

00:20:25.192 --> 00:20:28.262
[INOJIN] <i>Hey... come on... you-!</i>

00:20:28.295 --> 00:20:32.533
Stop it! Seriously! Come on!

00:20:32.566 --> 00:20:33.667
You keep moving...

00:20:33.700 --> 00:20:37.437
and you're only gonna make your
injuries worse!

00:20:37.471 --> 00:20:40.140
Ino... jin...

00:20:40.974 --> 00:20:42.109
(STUNNED)

00:20:58.325 --> 00:20:59.993
Inojin...

00:21:04.298 --> 00:21:08.135
[INOJIN] <i>What an idiot, huh?</i>
<i>Coming all the way here...</i>

00:21:08.168 --> 00:21:12.472
<i>...just when things are</i>
<i>at their most dangerous...</i>

00:21:12.506 --> 00:21:16.310
